        <num>CC 389</num>
        <heading>PERSONS UNABLE TO CARE FOR THEIR</heading>
        <content>
          <p>TITLE IX.  PERSONS UNABLE TO CARE FOR THEIR
PERSONS OR PROPERTY
CHAPTER 1.  GROUNDS FOR INTERDICTION
Art. 389.  Full interdiction
A court may order the full interdiction of a natural person of the age of majority, or an emancipated minor, who due to an infirmity, is unable consistently to make reasoned decisions regarding the care of his person and property, or to communicate those decisions, and whose interests cannot be protected by less restrictive means.</p>
        </content>
